AB  - Blair Wimbush, NS vice president  for real estate and the railroads corporate sustainability officer, said setting its emission-reduction goal is an important step toward fulfillment of Norfolk Southern's objective to achieve industry leadership in environmentally responsible business practices. Disclosing our carbon footprint last year was the first step. Now, we move forward with an aggressive yet realistic goal, and we have the tools to measure our progress toward attaining it."In 2009, NS hauled 158.5 billion ton-miles of freight, producing 4.7 million metric tons of greenhouse gases mainly from its diesel-burning locomotives. That produced emissions per revenue ton-mile of 30 grams. Cutting emissions 10 percent in five years would bring them to 27 grams per revenue ton-mile for the same freight volume, NS said, and put 475,000 fewer metric tons into the atmosphere a year by 2014.
